27/04/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The government approved an agreement with the United States on preventing weapons of mass destruction, it was reported Friday (25 April). 
The agreement also stipulates measures to enhance co-operation in the military and defence sector.
In other news, a delegation from Macedonia's Parliament visited Tirana on Friday, discussing joint efforts for EU and NATO accession. 
The group met first with Albanian Parliament Speaker Servet Pellumbi, then with President Alfred Moisiu, Prime Minister Fatos Nano and Defence Minister Pandeli Majko. 
(ATA, MIA - 25/04/03)
